  "original_title": "\u0b87\u0bb2\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc8 \u0b89\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0ba9\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbe\u0b95 \u0b85\u0bb5\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0ba9\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bcb\u0bae\u0bcd - \u0baa\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0ba9\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "We are closely monitoring the situation in Sri Lanka - Britain",
      "author": "Digital Desk 5",
      "body_lines": [
        "Britain has said that it is closely monitoring the events taking place in Sri Lanka. In addition, Britain has also emphasized that those participating in the demonstration and the security forces should observe moderation in these cases.",
        "The British High Commissioner to Sri Lanka, Sarah Houlton, and the country's Minister of Foreign Affairs, Tariq Ahmed, have said this in a Twitter post as anti-government protests have intensified in areas including the capital, Colombo.",
        "High Commissioner Sarah Houlton has posted on Twitter about the protests taking place in the country, \"The British government is watching the events happening in Sri Lanka very closely. Peaceful protest and freedom of expression are vital to Sri Lanka's democracy. ' has mentioned.",
        "At the same time, the British Minister of Foreign Affairs said in his Twitter post, \"The situation in Sri Lanka is worrying. Peaceful protests must be protected. Demonstrators and security forces should exercise restraint. We can find solutions by working together.",
        "It is noteworthy that Britain has issued a travel warning to avoid traveling to Sri Lanka except for essential needs after a police curfew was issued to some police units in Colombo with effect from 9 pm yesterday."
      ],
